// ── @P primitives — n=6 axiomatic basis (atlas grade [11*]) ──

@P HEXALANG-N6-UNIQUENESS = sigma(n)·phi(n) = n·tau(n) <==> n=6 :: hexa_lang_axiom [11*]
  => unique-identity theorem. sigma(6)·phi(6) = 12·2 = 24 = 6·4 = n·tau(6). 모든 hexa-lang design constant 가 이 식 의 산술적 귀결. README.md: "Zero arbitrary choices. Every constant derived from n = 6."
  |> README.md (lines 13-15) + doc/n6-constants.md sec "Core Theorem"

@P HEXALANG-EGYPTIAN-MEMORY = 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/6 = 1 :: hexa_lang_memory_axiom [11*]
  => 완전수 6 의 unit-fraction decomposition 이 memory model partition axiom. Stack:Heap:Arena = 3:2:1 (no-waste, sum=1). own/borrow/move/drop = tau=4 lifecycle keywords. README "Egyptian memory" pillar.
  |> doc/spec.md sec 8 + README.md line 68

@P HEXALANG-ZERO-ARBITRARY-CHOICE = "every integer in the language comes from arithmetic of 6" :: hexa_lang_meta_axiom [11*]
  => language design 의 self-imposed constraint. arbitrary tunable hyperparameter = 0. 14/14 design constants EXACT (DSE v2 21,952 enumerated combos, 100% match). Pareto score 0.7854.
  |> README.md line 17 + doc/n6-constants.md sec "Constant Mapping" + spec.md sec 1 DSE


