@X HEXALANG-X-DOC-DRIFT-OPERATOR-COUNT = grammar.jsonl(46, 9 groups) vs spec.md(24, 6 groups, J2) vs reference.md(24+slice/range extensions) :: hexa_lang_drift [7]
  => grammar.jsonl section=operators count=46 (formula 6+6+4+6+8+4+4+4+4 = 46) — adds shift (<<,>>), compound assign (+=, -=, *=, /=, ??=, ||=), null-safe (??, ?., |>, ...), type-check (in, is, as, typeof), slice (:, [:], [:n], [n:]). spec.md sec 4 canonical 24=J2(6). reference.md sec "Assignment & Special" includes ..= + => (extras). drift = grammar evolution beyond spec freeze.
  |> grammar.jsonl line 4 + spec.md sec 4 + reference.md sec "Operators (24)"

